The paper focuses on enhancing the visual quality of GIF images through learning-based methods, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as color dequantization and temporal interpolation. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of large datasets, which suggests machine learning (ML) techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with graphics formats and visual artifacts, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category. The use of a novel CNN architecture and comprehensive loss function suggests a focus on deep learning (DL), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of state-of-the-art approaches, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
